                <h1>Is Deferred Adjudication Considered a Conviction?</h1>
                <p>Deferred adjudication is not considered a formal conviction. Instead, it is a legal alternative where charges are deferred pending successful completion of certain conditions, like probation. If the individual meets these conditions, the charges can be dismissed, allowing them to avoid a conviction on their record.</p>
